Reality is something real
Real is something that is true
True is something that is not false
False is...
See?... 
Not that simple...

For me, the reality and the truth can be divide into 3 categories:

1.- personal reality: the things that is real or true only for you (your way to see the world, your interpretation)

2.- the common reality: the things that are real or true in a social level (to the community), but it is still  relative between communities (very important, without a good definition of this reality the societies could collapse)

3.- the definitive reality: that is a mystery, this is the goal of the science, philosophy and others fields of study (solve this mystery)... But at the end we know that is "almost" impossible to reach... it's like reach the perfection... 

Now, "woman"... That is a word... words exist to describe something common between the members of a community... a common way to call or name something... It is a definition... a social construction...

The "words" in all the live languages, change with time...

To have a real dialogue, we need to define the goals of the discussion.
